CRIMEAN-CONGO HEMORRHAGIC FEVER (07): PAKISTAN (PUNJAB)
*******************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Sat 12 Sep 2020
Source: The News International [edited]
https://www.thenews.com.pk/print/713616-congo-virus-claims-life


A Congo-virus patient from Sheikhupura [Punjab] died in the Mayo Hospital on Friday [11 Sep 2020]. A spokesperson for the Primary & Secondary Healthcare Department (P&SHD) said a butcher had been under treatment at the Mayo Hospital for the last 5 days. P&SHD Secretary Capt (Retd) Muhammad Usman said the department had traced 15 people who had been in contact with the victim. He added the deceased had caught the virus from animals.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The report above indicates that the fatal case had occupational exposure to infected cattle or carcasses, which may have been the source of infection.

Pakistan has confirmed cases of CCHF in almost every province: Sindh (Karachi), Punjab (Faisalabad, Multan, and Rawalpindi), Balochistan (Quetta), and Khyber Pakhtunkhwa (Peshawar). There is a need to educate the general public, farmers, and healthcare workers about the causes, transmission, and risks of CCHF and advise on practical preventive measures. - Mod.UBA

HealthMap/ProMED map of Pakistan: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7780237,35329]
